        "name": "Brute Force",
        "time": "O(n²)",
        "space": "O(1)",
        "code": "def max_subarray(nums):\n    best = nums[0]\n    for i in range(len(nums)):\n        s = 0\n        for j in range(i, len(nums)):\n            s += nums[j]\n            best = max(best, s)\n    return best",
        "explanation": "Try every starting index, sum forward. Correct but quadratic."
      },
      {
        "name": "Kadane's Algorithm",
        "time": "O(n)",
        "space": "O(1)",
        "code": "def max_subarray(nums):\n    best = cur = nums[0]\n    for x in nums[1:]:\n        cur = max(x, cur + x)\n        best = max(best, cur)\n    return best",
        "explanation": "At each index, decide: extend the previous subarray, or start fresh from here? Track running best. The key insight: if the previous sum is negative, it's useless — start fresh."
      }
    ]
